This paper is about improving neural conversational models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper specifically addresses the challenges of working with dialogue data, which is a subfield of NLP. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a weighting model to improve the performance of the neural conversational models, which involves machine learning techniques such as parameter estimation and empirical loss minimization. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also evaluates its approach using unsupervised metrics, which could make it relevant to categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SD (Sound).
